<extrachapter>
  <title>Experimental</title>
 
  <section>
  <title>Introduction</title>
  <body>

  <p>
	Our development of new and exiting stuff is done in the experimental java 
	subversion repository. You can find it at <uri>http://www.gentooexperimental.org/svn/java/</uri>.
    If you are looking to help out, check out the experimental tree and have
    a look around.  
  </p>

  </body>
  </section>  

  <section>
  <title>Experimental overlay</title>
  <body>
      
  <p>
    The experimental Java tree is available through SVN at:
    <uri>https://gentooexperimental.org/svn/java/gentoo-java-experimental</uri>.
    <br/>  
    At the moment of writing it contains mostly modulized jboss
    packages, spring packages along with some updates to misc packages
    by our padawan nichoj.  
  </p>

  <p>
    In order to use the experimental tree on your machine, you need to perform the following steps

    <pre caption="Using the experimental tree">
    <comment>If you don't have subversion installed yet, you need to start by emerging it:</comment>
    # <i>emerge subversion</i>
  
    # <i>mkdir -p /usr/local/overlays/java-experimental</i>
    # <i>svn co https://gentooexperimental.org/svn/java/gentoo-java-experimental /usr/local/overlays/java-experimental</i>
    </pre>
    Edit <path>/etc/make.conf</path> and add <path>/usr/local/overlays/java-experimental</path> to PORTDIR_OVERLAY, 
    i.e. PORTDIR_OVERLAY="/usr/local/portage /usr/local/overlays/java-experimental" 
  </p>

  <p>
    Then you should be all set to emerge stuff from the experimental tree.
  </p>

  </body>
  </section>

  <section>
  <title>1.5 Overlay</title>
  <body>
    
  <p>
    Some rather big changes are needed to get 1.5 unmasked, axxo is working on this in his overlay.
  </p>

  <p>
    Most important changes are:
    <ul>
      <li>merge time vm switching(#86900)</li>
      <li>merge time build.xml rewriting (#86903)</li>
      <li>axxo's branch of the java-config-ng started by compnerd</li>
      <li>Uses symlinks instead of PATH hacks to choose betwean user/system vm, which is more flexible.</li>
      <li>Removal of jikes useflag, you can now easily choose betwean javac/eclipse-ecj/jikes</li>
    </ul>
  And a variation of other bugs, you can find a list <uri link="http://www.gentooexperimental.org/svn/java/axxo-overlay/README/bugs-this-fixed">here</uri>
    But there is still some work todo, you can find an ever changing todo list <uri link="http://www.gentooexperimental.org/svn/java/axxo-overlay/README/todo">here</uri>
  </p>

  <p>
    Work has also started on updated documentation that go along with this overlay:
    <ul>
      <li><uri link="http://www.gentooexperimental.org/svn/java/axxo-overlay/README/docs/java-devel.html">Gentoo Java Packaging Guide</uri></li>
      <li><uri link="http://www.gentooexperimental.org/svn/java/axxo-overlay/README/docs/java-user.html">Gentoo Java User Guide</uri></li>
    </ul>
  </p>

  <p>
    <mail link="axxo@gentoo.org">axxo</mail> would really appreciate any comments/suggestions/fixes/patches to improve any of these
  </p>

  </body>
  </section>  

  <section>
  <title>Eclipse overlay</title>
  <body>
    
  <p>
    One of our users, Chewi, made huge changes to the eclipse eclass,
    and packaged a lot of eclipse plugins, you can find his word in the 
    <uri link="http://www.gentooexperimental.org/svn/java/chewi-overlay/">chewi-overlay</uri>.
    He has a readme <uri link="http://www.gentooexperimental.org/svn/java/chewi-overlay/README.txt">here</uri>.
  </p>

  </body>
  </section>

  <section>
  <title>java-config-ng</title>
  <body>
	<p>
		Compnerd started java-config-ng as an attempt to improve the current java-config.
    	You can find it here <uri>http://www.gentooexperimental.org/svn/java/java-config-ng/</uri>
	</p>
    <p>
		axxo started a branch to add functionality to support things needed for the 1.5 overlay
		and generally make things work, you can find it at
	    <uri>http://www.gentooexperimental.org/svn/java/java-config-ng/branches/axxo/</uri>
    </p>

  </body>
  </section>
</extrachapter>

